One of the country’s largest energy firms said it was likely to freeze prices until 2015 after George Osborne unveiled plans to reduce green levies.

Ahead of his Autumn Statement this week the Chancellor gave details of reforms which he said would see £50 shaved off energy bills.

He also announced new handouts of up to £1,000 for homeowners to spend on insulation and energy-efficient boilers - saying it would be funded by a fresh crackdown on tax avoidance.

